      "content": "i get that there are two sides, but i'm asking for more than just a summary of the debate. like, when you look at the actual outcomes in places that have it vs places that don't, isn't it pretty clear that the \"right\" side is the one that actually works for people? doesn't the human rights argument carry more weight than just economic efficiency?",
